The paper deals with the computational complexity of a fundamental concept in communication complexity, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science. The paper provides an algorithm for approximating the information complexity of an arbitrary function, which is a problem in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the convergence rate of the information complexity of a function, which involves information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm involves data structures and algorithms for computing the information complexity, which could fall under data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the geometric interpretation of the information complexity, which could fall under computational geometry (cs.CG).
